The Comptroller-General of Customs Strike Force, Team ‘A’, has intercepted prohibited goods worth N6.6billion in the last eight weeks and arrested three suspected smugglers. The team, it was gathered, also generated over N1.3 as revenue for the months of March and April, this year, through the issuance of demand notices (DN) to ensure complete payments of duties and penalties for underpayment.   Nigeria, others need $106b finance for agric     VFD Group increases dividend     Ngige: growing poverty responsible for child labour   Addressing reporters at government warehouse in Ikeja and Ikorodu yesterday,  Coordinator of the Strike force, Deputy Comptroller Mohammed Sani Yusuf told reporters that his team raked in money and seized prohibited goods worth about N8 billion for the Federal Government in the last eight weeks. He said that the prohibited items were seized based on their resolve to step up their fight against smuggling and enemies of the nation’s economy. Yusuf, while showcasing the items in Ikeja and  Ikorodu, Lagos, said the team in a renewed vigour seized 1,030 slabs of donkey skin, 387kg of cannabis sativa, 285 bales of used clothes and 4,000 bags of foreign parboiled rice (an equivalent of about 7 truck loads) within the period of eight weeks.